FBIS4-34218 "drlat117aa_94006" FBIS-LAT-94-117 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Ibero-American Leaders Meet, View Summit Results Ibero-American Leaders Meet, View Summit Results Dominican Vice President on Haitian Situation PA1606172294 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network in Spanish 1409 GMT 16 Jun 94 PA1606172294 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network Spanish BFN [Report on interview with Dominican Vice President Carlos Morales Troncoso by unidentified reporter in Cartagena de Indias on 16 June -- recorded] [Text] [Reporter] Amid complications, restrictions, and endless competition with the local media, we were able to approach Dominican Vice President Carlos Morales, and ask him about the Cuban [as heard] situation. [Morales] What is not being said is that we, Dominicans, are the hardest hit by the Haitian situation. As a result of the continuing Haitian problem, our country has over 1 million illegal Haitian residents, which constitutes an extremely heavy burden. We support a prompt, but democratic solution.
